author: detroitnews.com
title: Daniel Cleary declines to report to Grand Rapids
text:
Daniel Cleary refuses to report to minor league Grand Rapids. (Photo: David Guralnick / Detroit News) 
CONNECT 2 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Forward Daniel Cleary cleared waivers and has told general manager Ken Holland he will not report to the minor league affiliate Grand Rapids Griffins.
Holland said there are no salary cap ramifications for the team — Cleary’s salary this season is $950,000 — and doesn’t know what Cleary’s plans are going further forward.
“You’ll have to ask him,” Holland said .”He told Kris Draper (Red Wings executive) and myself that he’s not reporting to Grand Rapids.”
